## Translations (i18n)

All user-facing strings MUST live in `i18n/en.ts`, not hardcoded in JSX.

```typescript
// i18n/en.ts
export const en = {
  signup: {
    heading: 'Start your family journey today',
    subtitle: 'Join our community to manage schedules.',
    createAccount: 'Create Account',
  },
};

// In component:
import { en } from '../../i18n';
const t = en;
<h1>{t.signup.heading}</h1>
```

## Component Render Pattern

Split large JSX into named render functions. Never return one giant block.

```typescript
// BAD - one massive return
return (
  <Layout>
    {/* 100+ lines of mixed JSX */}
  </Layout>
);

// GOOD - split into logical sections
const renderOAuthButtons = () => ( /* ... */ );
const renderForm = () => ( /* ... */ );
const renderFooter = () => ( /* ... */ );

return (
  <Layout>
    {renderOAuthButtons()}
    {renderForm()}
    {renderFooter()}
  </Layout>
);
```

Each render function should be **one clear responsibility** (e.g., form, buttons, footer).

## MUI Component Rules

**Always use MUI components, not raw HTML elements:**

### Layout Components
- `<Box>` instead of `<div>` (for containers, wrappers, layout)
- `<Paper>` or `<Card>` instead of `<div className={styles.card}>` (for elevated surfaces)
- `<Container>` for max-width centering
- `<Stack>` for flexbox layouts

```typescript
// BAD - raw divs with SCSS
<div className={styles.page}>
  <div className={styles.card}>
    <h1>Title</h1>
  </div>
</div>

// GOOD - MUI components
<Box className={styles.page}>
  <Paper className={styles.card}>
    <Typography variant="h5">Title</Typography>
  </Paper>
</Box>
```

### Typography Components
Use MUI `<Typography>` instead of raw HTML text elements (`h1`вЂ“`h6`, `p`, `span`).
Use MUI `<Link>` or React Router `<Link>` instead of raw `<a>` tags.

```typescript
// BAD
<h1 className={styles.heading}>Title</h1>
<p className={styles.subtitle}>Subtitle</p>
<a href="/">Link</a>

// GOOD
<Typography variant="h5" component="h1">Title</Typography>
<Typography variant="body2" color="text.secondary">Subtitle</Typography>
<Link href="/" underline="hover" color="primary">Link</Link>
```

- `variant` controls the visual style (font size, weight, line height) from theme
- `component` controls the rendered HTML element (for SEO/accessibility)
- `color` uses theme tokens (`text.primary`, `text.secondary`, `primary.main`)
- Only use raw HTML for: `<form>`, `<label>` (form inputs), `<button type="submit">` when not using MUI Button

## Styling Rules

1. Use MUI components + theme tokens first
2. SCSS Modules only for layout, gradients, responsive, or things MUI can't do
3. No inline styles except MUI `sx` prop for small one-off tweaks
4. Colors come from theme, not hardcoded (exception: SCSS gradients may use theme color values)

## Component Rules

- Functional components only
- One component per file
- Each folder has an `index.ts` re-export
- Props interface defined above the component
- Hooks at the top, handlers next, render functions last, return at the bottom
